With wet weather in full force across the city, Manenberg saw a slow start to the 2019 elections. All stations maintained a strong police presence, alert for possible gang violence. Short lines provided a smooth voting process for those present with presiding officers reporting no hiccups.  To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
